% Question 1 (5 points) - Using the family relations defined above, write a structure that defines mother(X, Y) as "X is Y's mother".
% Uncomment and complete the below stub. See Prolog slides on Blackboard for a hint.
mother(X, Y) :- parent(X, Y), female(X). % X is a parent of Y, and X is female
	

% Question 2 (5 points) - Using the family relations defined above, write a structure that defines sister(X,Y) as "X is Y's sister".
% Uncomment and complete the below stub. Use dif(X,Y) to check that X and Y are not the same person
sister(X, Y) :- dif(X, Y), female(X), parent(PARENT, X), parent(PARENT, Y), female(PARENT). % X isn't Y, X is female, and X and Y have a parent in common. Get just one answer by only accepting parents who are female


% Question 3 (10 points) - Define max(X, L) as "X is the largest element in list L".
